# SafeFloor Industrial IoT Safety Platform: Wearable Integration Module Specification

**Document Version:** 1.1 (Update to v1.0 for Wearable Expansion)  
**Author:** Senior Technical Architect, Meridian Systems  
**Date:** [Current Date]  
**Project Phase:** Module Expansion (9 months into 14-month engagement)  
**Client:** AmeriSteel Manufacturing  
**Status:** Finalized specification for wearable integration module, enhancing individual worker safety monitoring. This builds on the existing AI safety monitoring platform (live environmental detection with 43% OSHA incident reduction). The addition integrates smart badge data for personalized alerts, fatigue detection, and compliance with OSHA PEL limits (e.g., noise exposure < 90 dBA over 8 hours). All components align with client policies on data privacy (anonymized worker IDs) and real-time processing (latency < 1s for proximity alerts).  

This specification details the wearable data pipeline for ingestion and processing, the fatigue detection algorithm, and the supervisor notification flow. Integration leverages the existing Kafka-based streaming infrastructure, with new edge gateways for UWB positioning and biometric processing. The system supports 2,200 workers across 3 shifts, with data anonymization to comply with HIPAA-like standards for health metrics.

## 1. Overview
The wearable integration module extends the platform to monitor individual workers via smart badges. Key features:
- **Data Sources:** Smart badges providing location, proximity, biometrics (heart rate, skin temperature), and noise exposure.
- **Detection Capabilities:** Proximity alerts, heat stress, cumulative noise tracking, fatigue (based on heart rate and movement variability).
- **Outputs:** Real-time alerts to worker badges (e.g., vibration for proximity), supervisor notifications for fatigue/heat stress, and dashboard updates.
- **Tech Stack:** Kafka for streaming, TensorFlow for fatigue ML model, PostgreSQL for OSHA PEL tracking and historical data, MQTT for badge-to-gateway communication, React-based dashboard extensions for supervisors.
- **Scalability:** Handles 2,200 concurrent badge streams at 1Hz sampling rate, with peak throughput of 5,000 events/sec.
- **Security:** End-to-end encryption (TLS 1.3 for streams, AES-256 for stored biometrics), anonymized worker IDs (e.g., hashed UUIDs), RBAC for supervisor access.
- **Integration Points:** Merges with existing anomaly detection (e.g., correlating worker location with environmental hazards) and alert engine.

## 2. Data Models
Data models extend the existing Sensor Data Event schema (from v1.0) for wearables. All models use JSON Schema for validation.

### 2.1 Wearable Data Event
Represents raw data from smart badges.
```json
{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "eventId": { "type": "string", "description": "Unique UUID" },
    "timestamp": { "type": "string", "format": "date-time" },
    "sourceType": { "type": "string", "enum": ["wearable_badge"] },
    "workerId": { "type": "string", "description": "Anonymized hashed ID (e.g., SHA-256 of employee number)" },
    "location": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "zone": { "type": "string", "description": "Plant zone (e.g., 'Assembly Line 3')" },
        "coordinates": { "type": "array", "items": { "type": "number" }, "minItems": 3, "maxItems": 3, "description": "[x, y, z] in UWB coordinate system" },
        "proximity": {
          "type": "array",
          "items": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
              "entity": { "type": "string", "enum": ["heavy_equipment", "hazmat_zone"] },
              "distance": { "type": "number", "description": "Meters" },
              "alertThreshold": { "type": "number", "description": "Safe distance (e.g., 2m)" }
            },
            "required": ["entity", "distance"]
          }
        }
      },
      "required": ["zone", "coordinates"]
    },
    "biometrics": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "heartRate": { "type": "number", "description": "BPM" },
        "skinTemperature": { "type": "number", "description": "Celsius" },
        "movementVariability": { "type": "number", "description": "Standard deviation of acceleration over 5-min window (m/s²)" }
      }
    },
    "noiseExposure": {
      "type": "object",
      "properties": {
        "instantNoise": { "type": "number", "description": "Current dBA" },
        "cumulativeDose": { "type": "number", "description": "Percentage of OSHA PEL (e.g., 100% = 90 dBA for 8 hours)" },
        "timeWeightedAverage": { "type": "number", "description": "TWA dBA over shift" }
      }
    }
  },
  "required": ["eventId", "timestamp", "sourceType", "workerId", "location", "biometrics", "noiseExposure"]
}
```

### 2.2 Fatigue Detection Result
Output from the fatigue algorithm, extending the Anomaly Detection Result schema.
```json
{
  "$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#",
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "anomalyId": { "type": "string", "description": "Unique UUID" },
    "timestamp": { "type": "string", "format": "date-time" },
    "type": { "type": "string", "enum": ["fatigue", "heat_stress", "noise_overexposure", "proximity_violation"] },
    "confidence": { "type": "number", "minimum": 0, "maximum": 1 },
    "details": { "type": "object", "additionalProperties": { "type": "string" }, "description": "e.g., {'heartRate': '95 BPM', 'movementVar': '0.2 m/s²'}" },
    "workerId": { "type": "string", "description": "Anonymized ID" },
    "relatedEvents": { "type": "array", "items": { "type": "string" } }
  },
  "required": ["anomalyId", "timestamp", "type", "confidence", "workerId"]
}
```

